1
00:02:17,904 --> 00:02:21,067
<i>(very quietly)</i>
Who'll pinch me to wake me up?

2
00:02:26,379 --> 00:02:29,143
Who will laugh at me when l fall?

3
00:02:33,019 --> 00:02:35,613
Whose breath will l listen for...

4
00:02:38,391 --> 00:02:41,417
...so that l may sleep?

5
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:44,787
Whose hand will l hold...

6
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:49,792
...so that l may walk?

7
00:03:04,751 --> 00:03:12,180
<i>(man) We may question ourselves</i>
<i>at moments such as these.</i>

8
00:03:13,894 --> 00:03:16,590
<i>Did we make the right decision</i>
<i>to settle here?</i>

9
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:30,808
We are grateful for the time
we have been given.

10
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,723
<i>(murmuring)</i>

11
00:03:48,662 --> 00:03:50,493
<i>(thunderclap)</i>

12
00:03:52,132 --> 00:03:53,963
<i>(moaning)</i>

13
00:05:57,023 --> 00:05:58,854
<i>(rumbling)</i>

14
00:06:18,645 --> 00:06:22,206
What manner of spectacle has attracted
your attention so splendidly?

15
00:06:22,282 --> 00:06:26,480
l ought to carry it in my pocket
to help me teach.

16
00:06:27,921 --> 00:06:29,912
<i>(flies buzzing)</i>

17
00:06:34,594 --> 00:06:36,926
Who came upon this?

18
00:06:40,633 --> 00:06:44,034
- Philip, did you move this?
- No, Mr. Walker.

19
00:06:44,104 --> 00:06:46,095
<i>(flies buzzing)</i>

20
00:06:52,579 --> 00:06:56,640
l inspected it carefully. lts head was
twisted back and much of its fur removed.

21
00:06:56,716 --> 00:07:00,083
- l see.
- lt was murdered.

22
00:07:00,153 --> 00:07:02,485
But who is the culprit?

23
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:06,116
Who has done this heinous act?

24
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:10,595
- Those We Don't Speak Of killed it.
- There it is.

25
00:07:10,663 --> 00:07:14,429
Why would such a notion
come into your mind?

26
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:17,827
- They're meat eaters.
- Mmm.

27
00:07:17,904 --> 00:07:20,930
They have large claws.

28
00:07:21,007 --> 00:07:22,998
Children...

29
00:07:23,076 --> 00:07:28,946
...Those We Don't Speak Of have not
breached our borders for many years.

30
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:33,144
We do not go into their woods,

31
00:07:33,219 --> 00:07:36,450
they do not come into our valley.

32
00:07:36,523 --> 00:07:38,514
lt is a truce.

33
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:41,082
We do not threaten them.

34
00:07:41,161 --> 00:07:43,152
Why would they do this?

35
00:07:43,229 --> 00:07:48,257
And we ought not to overlook
the Flight of the Birds.

36
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:52,771
We didn't have it last year
and l, for one, missed it desperately.

37
00:07:54,174 --> 00:07:59,009
And l know your wife missed
the children dressed in feathers and such.

38
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:01,570
- l am fond of it.
- Mmm.

39
00:08:02,715 --> 00:08:05,047
l do not have a say in this matter.

40
00:08:05,118 --> 00:08:07,746
August Nicholson is chair
of today's meeting.

41
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:10,187
<i>(door opens)</i>

42
00:08:10,256 --> 00:08:15,193
There's a young man who has
requested a word with the elders.

43
00:08:15,261 --> 00:08:17,752
Well, do have him come forward.

44
00:08:19,699 --> 00:08:21,530
Alice.

45
00:08:24,571 --> 00:08:27,438
<i>(August)</i> Hello, Lucius.

46
00:08:32,645 --> 00:08:36,604
''My mother is unaware
of the reason for my visit today.''

47
00:08:36,683 --> 00:08:42,121
''She did not give her consent
or consult me in any form.''

48
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:48,851
''The passing of little
Daniel Nicholson from illness,

49
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:51,795
and other events,
have weighed on my thoughts.''

50
00:08:52,632 --> 00:08:56,090
''l ask permission to cross
into the forbidden woods

51
00:08:56,169 --> 00:08:58,296
and travel to the nearest town.''

52
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:02,535
''l will gather new medicines,
and l will return.''

53
00:09:02,609 --> 00:09:05,339
''With regards to
Those We Don't Speak Of,

54
00:09:05,411 --> 00:09:08,073
l am certain they will let me pass.''

55
00:09:08,148 --> 00:09:12,778
''Creatures can sense emotion and fear.''

56
00:09:12,852 --> 00:09:16,549
''They will see l am pure of intention,
and not afraid.''

57
00:09:16,623 --> 00:09:18,614
''The end.''

58
00:09:26,166 --> 00:09:29,033
<i>(Alice) What goes on</i>
<i>in that head of yours?</i>

59
00:09:31,571 --> 00:09:33,869
Say something, Lucius.

60
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:42,111
Finton Coin is in the tower,
and l've promised to sit with him.

61
00:09:42,182 --> 00:09:44,173
Hmm.

62
00:09:46,553 --> 00:09:49,784
Do you ever think of the towns, Finton?

63
00:09:49,856 --> 00:09:52,324
The towns?

64
00:09:52,392 --> 00:09:55,054
What for?

65
00:09:55,128 --> 00:09:59,428
They're wicked places
where wicked people live. That's all.

66
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:07,970
Thank you, Lucius.

67
00:10:08,041 --> 00:10:10,202
You're a good friend.

68
00:10:14,180 --> 00:10:17,616
l do hope no one saw you.

69
00:10:17,684 --> 00:10:19,515
<i>(howling)</i>

70
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:33,622
<i>(flies buzzing)</i>

71
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:45,610
What we seem to have amongst us
is a predator of some type,

72
00:10:45,678 --> 00:10:49,842
most likely a coyote or a wolf.

73
00:10:51,751 --> 00:10:56,085
lts manner of... of killing
and removing the fur,

74
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:59,488
but leaving the flesh torn,

75
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:03,757
may be a sign that this animal
suffers from madness.

76
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:07,797
And for the next fortnight,
we should be vigilant

77
00:11:07,867 --> 00:11:10,301
for sightings of this coyote.

78
00:11:10,370 --> 00:11:14,864
Keep careful watch over
our little ones as they play on the hills.

79
00:11:18,911 --> 00:11:22,142
As for the other notion...

80
00:11:22,215 --> 00:11:26,584
...we do not believe
our boundary has been breached.

81
00:11:26,653 --> 00:11:33,217
Those We Don't Speak Of are much
larger creatures than coyotes...

82
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:37,720
...and we would know
if they had been here.

83
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:41,028
<i>(murmuring)</i>

84
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:43,227
<i>(door opens)</i>

85
00:11:43,303 --> 00:11:46,568
Ahh, it's frightful, this business
with the coyote. ls it not, Papa?

86
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:49,699
- Do not feel worried, Kitty.
- You are not troubled?

87
00:11:49,776 --> 00:11:52,176
l'm certain it will all end soon.

88
00:11:52,245 --> 00:11:57,012
- Can we speak on other matters, then?
- lt would be a relief.

89
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:59,142
l'm in love!

90
00:11:59,218 --> 00:12:02,881
l want your permission
to marry, Papa.

91
00:12:02,955 --> 00:12:05,423
There's a proper manner in which
things are supposed to happen.

92
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:08,085
Such as the boy would normally be
standing next to you,

93
00:12:08,161 --> 00:12:10,686
in a moment such as this...
Where is the boy in all this, Kitty?

94
00:12:10,763 --> 00:12:13,254
l haven't spoken to him as of yet.

95
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:17,099
The young man is unaware
of your intentions?

96
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:21,937
He has a quiet way. l was going to talk with
him, Papa, but not without your blessings.

97
00:12:22,008 --> 00:12:24,203
l won't talk with him without your blessings.

98
00:12:24,277 --> 00:12:25,676
Kitty!

99
00:12:25,745 --> 00:12:28,009
lt's Lucius Hunt.

100
00:12:30,983 --> 00:12:32,041
Lucius?

101
00:12:32,118 --> 00:12:35,178
You think badly of him?

102
00:12:35,254 --> 00:12:38,951
- No, no. l have been thinking about him.
- He's not like the other boys, Papa.

103
00:12:39,025 --> 00:12:41,084
He doesn't joke or bounce about.

104
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:43,390
No, he certainly does not.

105
00:12:45,431 --> 00:12:47,763
Do l have your blessings, then?

106
00:12:50,069 --> 00:12:52,060
<i>(sighs)</i>

107
00:12:54,507 --> 00:12:56,907
Look, do me one favor first.

108
00:12:56,976 --> 00:13:03,438
Do not tell anyone else of your burstings
until you have spoken with the young man.

109
00:13:09,155 --> 00:13:12,181
Good afternoon, Lucius.

110
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:19,323
l wanted to... to... to tell you something.

111
00:13:22,235 --> 00:13:24,567
l love you, Lucius.

112
00:13:26,239 --> 00:13:30,437
l love you... like the day is long.

113
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:33,104
l love you more than
the sun and the moon together.

114
00:13:33,179 --> 00:13:37,775
And if you feel the same way,
then we should not hide it any longer.

115
00:13:37,850 --> 00:13:41,684
lt's a gift, love is.
We should be thankful.

116
00:13:41,754 --> 00:13:45,986
We should bellow it out
with all the breath in our lungs.

117
00:13:46,058 --> 00:13:48,925
Thank you! Thank you!

118
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:51,395
Thank you!

119
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:57,034
<i>(screaming and sobbing)</i>

120
00:13:57,103 --> 00:13:59,867
Shh, shh.

121
00:13:59,939 --> 00:14:03,204
Shh.

122
00:14:03,276 --> 00:14:05,904
<i>(sobbing)</i>

123
00:14:05,978 --> 00:14:11,245
? Baby, sleep, gently sleep

124
00:14:11,317 --> 00:14:16,914
? Life is long and love is deep

125
00:14:16,989 --> 00:14:22,552
? Time will be sweet for thee

126
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:26,155
? All the world to see

127
00:14:26,232 --> 00:14:30,566
? Time to look about and know

128
00:14:30,636 --> 00:14:34,629
? How the shadows come and go

129
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:40,612
? How the breeze stirs the trees

130
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:45,014
? How the blossoms grow

131
00:14:56,095 --> 00:15:01,624
l often wondered if you and my son bonded
because neither of you is fond of speaking.

132
00:15:01,701 --> 00:15:03,760
You're very kind.

133
00:15:03,836 --> 00:15:07,829
You must pardon my manners.
l haven't slept in many nights.

134
00:15:16,082 --> 00:15:18,915
<i>(man)</i> You are doing capital,
Jamison.

135
00:15:18,985 --> 00:15:22,785
Just a few more moments, huh?
Gather your bravery.

136
00:15:22,855 --> 00:15:27,155
Do not jostle about so. You'll ruin my shirt.

137
00:15:27,226 --> 00:15:29,456
<i>(whimpering)</i>

138
00:15:29,529 --> 00:15:31,520
<i>(howling)</i>

139
00:15:32,632 --> 00:15:37,501
They made a sound when l made a sound,
and they mimic before they attack.

140
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:41,199
Have courage, man.
That's a wives' tale. lt isn't true.

141
00:15:41,274 --> 00:15:43,970
Do not falter. Steel yourself!

142
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:52,076
<i>(August) You know,</i>
<i>like a dog can smell you.</i>

143
00:15:52,151 --> 00:15:55,211
- Pardon me, Mr. Nicholson?
- Hmm.

144
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:02,659
You may run from sorrow, as we have.

145
00:16:02,728 --> 00:16:05,390
Sorrow will find you.

146
00:16:08,034 --> 00:16:10,764
lt can smell you.

147
00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,650
<i>(rustling)</i>

148
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:32,751
<i>(breathing heavily)</i>

149
00:16:37,029 --> 00:16:39,520
<i>(rustling continues)</i>

150
00:16:39,599 --> 00:16:41,430
<i>(footsteps)</i>

151
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:45,366
<i>(growl)</i>

152
00:16:45,438 --> 00:16:48,100
<i>(whimpering)</i>

153
00:16:48,174 --> 00:16:50,165
<i>(howling)</i>

154
00:16:51,944 --> 00:16:53,935
Hurry.

155
00:17:00,653 --> 00:17:03,781
l didn't know you could run so fast.

156
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,586
We're still for running and staying... Hey!

157
00:17:08,394 --> 00:17:13,593
<i>(Kitty) Noah ought to be punished. He</i>
<i>whacked little Joseph with a stick again.</i>

158
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:15,657
<i>(crowd groans)</i>

159
00:17:15,735 --> 00:17:18,169
- Ouch!
- <i>(girl)</i> No more hitting! Put it down!

160
00:17:18,237 --> 00:17:20,467
Ow, ow, ow!

161
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,507
<i>(girl #2)</i> Why don't they grab it?

162
00:17:22,608 --> 00:17:24,769
<i>(distant shouting)</i>

163
00:17:33,653 --> 00:17:35,848
<i>(woman)</i> Noah Percy!

164
00:17:36,856 --> 00:17:39,552
Stop your fussing right this moment.

165
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:42,560
<i>(murmuring and laughing)</i>

166
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:54,399
You're in trouble, you know.

167
00:17:54,473 --> 00:17:58,637
- No hitting, no hitting.
- l'm to place you in the quiet room.

168
00:17:58,711 --> 00:18:01,475
Um, l'll cry quarts.

169
00:18:01,547 --> 00:18:06,007
- What if we strike a deal?
- Yeah, capital idea.

170
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:09,851
lt would be prudent to keep our deal
a secret. Can you do that?

171
00:18:09,922 --> 00:18:13,085
Can l keep a secret?
Like a church mouse.

172
00:18:14,894 --> 00:18:17,556
You needn't go to the quiet room
if you a take an oath

173
00:18:17,630 --> 00:18:20,963
to never strike any person again.

174
00:18:22,635 --> 00:18:25,263
- No hitting, no hitting.
- No. No hitting.

175
00:18:25,337 --> 00:18:26,736
- No hitting.
- No hitting.

176
00:18:26,806 --> 00:18:28,797
No hitting.

177
00:18:30,609 --> 00:18:32,941
The deal is struck.

178
00:18:38,751 --> 00:18:40,218
<i>(sighs)</i>

179
00:18:40,286 --> 00:18:42,584
We ought not return right away, huh?

180
00:18:42,655 --> 00:18:46,614
What shall we do
with our stolen time?

181
00:18:46,692 --> 00:18:48,353
- Hmm.
- Hmm.

182
00:18:48,427 --> 00:18:51,328
- Hmm. Shall we have a foot race?
- Yes.

183
00:18:51,397 --> 00:18:53,922
- Up the hill to the resting rock?
- No cheating.

184
00:18:53,999 --> 00:18:56,968
What a deeply scandalous thing to say.
l insist you take that back.

185
00:18:57,036 --> 00:18:59,368
ls that the school bell?

186
00:19:04,744 --> 00:19:06,735
<i>(shouting)</i>

187
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:09,178
lvy, you cheated!

188
00:19:09,248 --> 00:19:11,580
l know! l'm sorry!

189
00:19:12,818 --> 00:19:14,786
<i>(giggling)</i>

190
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:19,614
Whoo!

191
00:19:39,145 --> 00:19:42,171
My sister cried a lot.

192
00:19:43,649 --> 00:19:46,948
You wonder how l recognized you?

193
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:52,286
Some people - just a handful,
mind you - give off the tiniest color.

194
00:19:52,358 --> 00:19:55,657
lt's faint, like a haze.

195
00:19:55,728 --> 00:20:00,256
lt's the only thing
l ever see in the darkness.

196
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:02,664
Papa has it, too.

197
00:20:04,270 --> 00:20:07,103
Do you wonder what your color is?

198
00:20:07,173 --> 00:20:09,971
Well, that l won't tell you.
lt's not ladylike to speak of such things.

199
00:20:10,042 --> 00:20:12,237
You shouldn't even have asked.

200
00:20:12,311 --> 00:20:14,472
<i>(bird flying overhead)</i>

201
00:20:19,618 --> 00:20:22,348
You run like a boy.

202
00:20:23,923 --> 00:20:26,084
Thank you.

203
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:33,395
l know why you denied my sister.

204
00:20:35,334 --> 00:20:38,064
When l was younger...

205
00:20:38,137 --> 00:20:41,800
...you used to hold my arm
when l walked.

206
00:20:42,675 --> 00:20:46,133
Then suddenly, you stopped.

207
00:20:46,212 --> 00:20:50,080
One day, l even tripped
in your presence, and nearly fell.

208
00:20:50,149 --> 00:20:54,950
l was faking, of course,
but still, you did not hold me.

209
00:20:56,689 --> 00:20:58,850
Sometimes we don't do
things we want to do

210
00:20:58,924 --> 00:21:02,553
so that others won't know
we want to do them.

211
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,929
- What?
- <i>(frog croaks)</i>

212
00:21:15,007 --> 00:21:17,237
<i>(yelps and laughs)</i>

213
00:21:25,584 --> 00:21:28,951
What's this? Oh, berries.

214
00:21:29,021 --> 00:21:31,353
What a splendid present.

215
00:21:31,423 --> 00:21:33,414
<i>(Lucius)</i> Be cautious.

216
00:21:33,492 --> 00:21:35,824
You are holding the bad color.

217
00:21:42,568 --> 00:21:46,902
This color attracts Those We Don't
Speak Of. You must bury it.

218
00:21:49,241 --> 00:21:52,574
You ought not to pick
that color berry any more.

219
00:21:54,113 --> 00:21:56,308
He picked it from his pocket.

220
00:21:57,883 --> 00:22:01,512
What's wrong?
Your breathing has changed.

221
00:22:01,587 --> 00:22:04,351
<i>(Lucius)</i> l've never set eyes
on these before.

222
00:22:04,423 --> 00:22:08,189
You did not pick that now.
Where did you find this?

223
00:22:15,134 --> 00:22:16,624
''Today at Resting Rock,

224
00:22:16,702 --> 00:22:21,230
Noah Percy handed lvy Walker berries
of the bad color.''

225
00:22:21,307 --> 00:22:23,537
''When asked where
he found these berries,

226
00:22:23,609 --> 00:22:26,100
for they were not like
others l have seen,

227
00:22:26,178 --> 00:22:29,477
he pointed to the drawing
upon Resting Rock.''

228
00:22:30,783 --> 00:22:34,412
''<i>It is my belief that Noah Percy</i>
<i>has entered the woods,</i>

229
00:22:34,486 --> 00:22:37,887
<i>and has done so on many occasions.</i> ''

230
00:22:37,957 --> 00:22:41,393
''<i>It is also my belief that,</i>
<i>because of his innocence,</i>

231
00:22:41,460 --> 00:22:45,055
<i>those creatures who reside</i>
<i>in the woods did not harm him.</i> ''

232
00:22:45,130 --> 00:22:48,566
''This strengthens my feeling
that they will let me pass

233
00:22:48,634 --> 00:22:51,603
if they sense l am not a threat.''

234
00:22:52,504 --> 00:22:56,133
<i>(Alice) We shall speak of the town,</i>
<i>just this once,</i>

235
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:59,302
<i>and we shall never speak of it again.</i>

236
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:07,614
Your father left for the market
on a Tuesday,

237
00:23:07,686 --> 00:23:10,712
at a quarter past nine in the morning.

238
00:23:14,093 --> 00:23:20,089
He was found robbed and naked
in the filthy river, two days later.

239
00:23:26,171 --> 00:23:29,299
Why'd you tell me this blackness?

240
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:32,674
So you will know the nature
of what you desire.

241
00:23:34,013 --> 00:23:37,505
l do not desire it.
My intentions are true to my word.

242
00:23:37,583 --> 00:23:40,051
l think of nothing
but the people of this village.

243
00:23:40,119 --> 00:23:45,352
Forgive me.
l am but scared for my only son's life.

244
00:23:45,424 --> 00:23:48,757
l am not the one with secrets.

245
00:23:51,130 --> 00:23:53,189
What is your meaning?

246
00:23:54,867 --> 00:23:58,268
There are secrets
in every corner of this village.

247
00:23:59,271 --> 00:24:03,605
Do you not feel it? Do you not see it?

248
00:24:04,576 --> 00:24:06,168
That is for my own well-being,

249
00:24:06,245 --> 00:24:10,341
so the evil things from my past
are kept close and not forgotten.

250
00:24:10,416 --> 00:24:13,010
Forgetting would be to let them
be born again in another form.

251
00:24:13,085 --> 00:24:15,076
Then let us open it.

252
00:24:15,154 --> 00:24:17,554
No!

253
00:24:17,623 --> 00:24:20,387
Perhaps we should speak
with Edward Walker together.

254
00:24:20,459 --> 00:24:23,826
- He may be able...
- He hides, too.

255
00:24:23,896 --> 00:24:26,387
He hides his feelings for you.

256
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,131
Oh.

257
00:24:37,776 --> 00:24:39,903
Sometimes we don't do things,

258
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:43,914
yet others know we want to do things,
so we don't do them.

259
00:24:48,454 --> 00:24:51,287
What nonsense are you saying?

260
00:24:55,661 --> 00:24:58,994
You needn't worry.
Nothing will happen to me.

261
00:25:03,135 --> 00:25:06,332
You remind me of a colt sometimes.

262
00:25:13,712 --> 00:25:16,943
What makes you think
he has feelings for me?

263
00:25:21,186 --> 00:25:23,518
He never touches you.

264
00:27:06,558 --> 00:27:08,389
<i>(growling)</i>

265
00:27:12,431 --> 00:27:14,262
<i>(rustling)</i>

266
00:27:32,517 --> 00:27:34,348
<i>(growling)</i>

267
00:27:38,624 --> 00:27:41,149
There's no escape!

268
00:27:43,428 --> 00:27:46,397
Oh, hello.

269
00:27:46,465 --> 00:27:48,933
l was just playing a game with Noah.

270
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:52,095
The rascal must have gone
to hide in my house again.

271
00:27:52,170 --> 00:27:54,229
<i>(loudly)</i> Houses are against the rules!

272
00:27:54,306 --> 00:27:56,638
<i>(whispering)</i> He knows that.

273
00:27:59,278 --> 00:28:01,610
Are you all right?

274
00:28:03,982 --> 00:28:09,648
We're tending to the children tonight,
Kitty and l. l should be with her. Be well.

275
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:18,860
l heard my parents speaking of you.

276
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:23,230
l know of your request to go to the towns.

277
00:28:23,302 --> 00:28:27,568
l think it is noble,
but l do not think it is right.

278
00:28:27,639 --> 00:28:31,473
<i>(Lucius)</i> Are you not angry
you have no sight?

279
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:35,570
<i>(whispers)</i> l see the world, Lucius Hunt.

280
00:28:35,647 --> 00:28:37,979
Just not as you see it.

281
00:28:45,657 --> 00:28:48,751
What of Noah, then?

282
00:28:48,827 --> 00:28:53,560
What if there are medicines for Noah
that could help him be still and to learn?

283
00:28:53,632 --> 00:28:57,966
May we stop speaking of this?
lt is putting knots in my stomach.

284
00:29:03,041 --> 00:29:06,204
Kitty is to be married.

285
00:29:07,212 --> 00:29:12,912
She's found love, again,
with Christop Crane.

286
00:29:12,984 --> 00:29:15,544
You think it an odd choice, right?

287
00:29:15,620 --> 00:29:21,490
You know, he won't sit back in his chair
for fear of setting wrinkles on his shirts.

288
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:25,257
But he does have
a gentlemanly way about him...

289
00:29:25,330 --> 00:29:29,494
...and he does care for my sister deeply.

290
00:29:30,702 --> 00:29:33,102
l think Kitty is blessed.

291
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:39,276
l am blessed as well.

292
00:29:39,344 --> 00:29:42,541
My older sister is now spoken for.

293
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:45,845
l am now free to receive
interest from anyone...

294
00:29:47,953 --> 00:29:50,547
...who might have interest.

295
00:29:54,059 --> 00:29:56,527
<i>(children laughing)</i>

296
00:30:00,132 --> 00:30:03,363
<i>(Kitty)</i> l'm going to get you. Oh!

297
00:30:03,435 --> 00:30:06,836
l got you. l got you.
Can you fetch a blanket for me?

298
00:30:06,905 --> 00:30:09,396
<i>(Ivy)</i> Have you seen Noah?

299
00:30:24,389 --> 00:30:26,550
<i>(loud thump)</i>

300
00:30:27,893 --> 00:30:29,724
Lucius?

301
00:30:47,813 --> 00:30:49,872
Lucius?

302
00:30:51,783 --> 00:30:53,774
<i>(growling)</i>

303
00:30:53,852 --> 00:30:55,683
<i>(whimpers)</i>

304
00:31:03,662 --> 00:31:05,653
<i>(breathes heavily)</i>

305
00:31:35,327 --> 00:31:37,921
- <i>(man)</i> Hurry, to the cellar!
- <i>(woman)</i> Oh, good gracious!

306
00:31:37,996 --> 00:31:41,056
<i>(shouting and bell ringing)</i>

307
00:31:57,682 --> 00:32:00,276
- They're coming. They're coming.
- Close the door.

308
00:32:00,352 --> 00:32:01,910
- Noah, close the door, OK?
- They're coming.

309
00:32:01,987 --> 00:32:04,319
- Close the door.
- Coming!

310
00:32:06,591 --> 00:32:08,752
Here we go.

311
00:32:08,827 --> 00:32:11,796
- Noah, come on inside!
- <i>(Noah)</i> Come on inside!

312
00:32:13,031 --> 00:32:16,228
<i>(man)</i> Everyone, inside!
Everyone, inside!

313
00:32:30,148 --> 00:32:33,208
<i>(bell ringing)</i>

314
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,913
<i>(grunting)</i>

315
00:32:39,157 --> 00:32:43,685
- <i>(Noah)</i> They're coming. Come on in.
- Let's close the door.

316
00:32:43,762 --> 00:32:46,993
- <i>(Ivy)</i> Lucius is outside, walking.
- <i>(Noah)</i> They're coming.

317
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:51,695
He's inside safe somewhere!
Please, close the door!

318
00:32:53,672 --> 00:32:56,402
He'll come back to make sure we're safe.

319
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:59,102
lvy! lvy, please.

320
00:33:15,594 --> 00:33:17,425
<i>(scratching)</i>

321
00:33:18,296 --> 00:33:20,127
<i>(growling)</i>

322
00:33:27,606 --> 00:33:30,234
- <i>(Kitty)</i> Please.
- No.

323
00:33:31,509 --> 00:33:33,977
Don't let them in.

324
00:33:38,516 --> 00:33:40,347
<i>(grunting)</i>

325
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:43,150
<i>(growling)</i>

326
00:34:18,757 --> 00:34:20,918
Come on in.

327
00:34:22,427 --> 00:34:24,258
<i>(thumping)</i>

328
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:32,299
<i>(rumbling)</i>

329
00:34:37,876 --> 00:34:39,707
<i>(rustling)</i>

330
00:34:47,118 --> 00:34:48,517
<i>(thumping)</i>

331
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:50,918
<i>(loud thump and hinges creaking)</i>

332
00:35:02,834 --> 00:35:06,634
<i>(Walker) By the markings we find</i>
<i>this morning on our homes...</i>

333
00:35:09,007 --> 00:35:14,570
<i>...I feel they were warning us.</i>
<i>They acted as if threatened.</i>

334
00:35:14,646 --> 00:35:19,015
<i>(August) Creatures have never</i>
<i>attacked us without reason.</i>

335
00:35:19,084 --> 00:35:22,349
<i>Does anyone here know of a reason...</i>

336
00:35:23,488 --> 00:35:26,548
<i>...why these events may have occurred?</i>

337
00:35:34,199 --> 00:35:36,565
Who has written this note?

338
00:35:46,644 --> 00:35:48,635
<i>(clears throat)</i>

339
00:35:49,447 --> 00:35:52,075
''Please read so that all may hear.''

340
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,778
''l have brought this burden upon us.''

341
00:35:57,522 --> 00:36:01,686
''On the day before last,
l crossed the forbidden line

342
00:36:01,760 --> 00:36:04,092
- into Covington Woods...''
- <i>(crowd gasps)</i>

343
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:08,462
''...and was witnessed there
by Those We Don't Speak Of.''

344
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:11,400
''l am deeply sorry.''

345
00:36:11,469 --> 00:36:15,235
''l have shamed myself and my family.''

346
00:36:15,306 --> 00:36:19,072
''l pray that my actions
will cause no further pains.''

347
00:36:19,144 --> 00:36:22,409
''With deepest sorrow, Lucius Hunt.''

348
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:24,471
<i>(crowd murmuring)</i>

349
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:54,603
ls he in trouble?

350
00:36:54,679 --> 00:36:56,670
<i>(laughing)</i>

351
00:37:06,958 --> 00:37:09,552
Do not fret.

352
00:37:18,236 --> 00:37:22,297
You are fearless in a way
that l shall never know.

353
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:35,917
<i>(Walker)</i> We are grateful...

354
00:37:36,988 --> 00:37:39,388
...for the time we have been given.

355
00:37:39,457 --> 00:37:41,789
<i>(man)</i> Yes. Yes, indeed.

356
00:37:42,794 --> 00:37:45,661
<i>(all start talking)</i>

357
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:47,721
Cheers.

358
00:38:28,439 --> 00:38:30,999
<i>(distant singing)</i>

359
00:38:32,543 --> 00:38:35,273
l had an elder sister.

360
00:38:35,346 --> 00:38:38,213
Mrs. Clack, you've been keeping secrets.

361
00:38:39,784 --> 00:38:43,117
Oh, Kitty reminds me of her so.

362
00:38:45,456 --> 00:38:48,118
<i>(Ivy)</i> What manner of person was she?

363
00:38:49,861 --> 00:38:52,421
- Saucy.
- Oh.

364
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:54,988
And we fought endlessly.

365
00:38:59,904 --> 00:39:02,236
May l ask her name?

366
00:39:05,476 --> 00:39:09,503
Why did she not come
to Covington Woods?

367
00:39:13,318 --> 00:39:16,845
My sister did not live
past her 23rd birthday.

368
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:22,382
A group of men took her life
in an alley by our home.

369
00:39:26,230 --> 00:39:28,664
Please rise!

370
00:39:28,733 --> 00:39:30,724
Come on.

371
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:08,362
She's not going to squeeze
my shirt like that, is she?

372
00:40:10,875 --> 00:40:12,866
<i>(muffled conversation)</i>

373
00:40:20,351 --> 00:40:25,015
Many blessings
on this most joyous of days.

374
00:40:25,089 --> 00:40:27,649
lt was a rare and lovely ceremony,
was it not?

375
00:40:27,725 --> 00:40:29,716
Glorious.

376
00:40:31,996 --> 00:40:36,660
l saw your hand move to your eyes
on more than one occasion.

377
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:39,362
That must have been dust of some matter.

378
00:41:46,804 --> 00:41:49,034
<i>(scream)</i>

379
00:41:53,744 --> 00:41:55,735
<i>(scream)</i>

380
00:41:58,382 --> 00:42:00,111
<i>(scream)</i>

381
00:42:00,184 --> 00:42:03,085
<i>(boy)</i> Mr. Walker!

382
00:42:07,158 --> 00:42:09,820
- <i>(boy)</i> Mr. Walker!
- <i>(boy #2)</i> Mr. Walker!

383
00:42:09,894 --> 00:42:11,725
<i>(murmuring)</i>

384
00:42:12,864 --> 00:42:15,264
<i>(man)</i> Behind them.

385
00:42:15,333 --> 00:42:17,699
<i>(man #2)</i> How did she deal
with this brightness?

386
00:42:17,768 --> 00:42:20,794
<i>(woman)</i> Help us out.

387
00:42:20,872 --> 00:42:22,772
<i>(man #3)</i> Where are
the rest of them?

388
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:29,372
Speak up.

389
00:42:30,615 --> 00:42:32,913
- They're in the village.
- What?

390
00:42:32,984 --> 00:42:35,145
They left more warnings.

391
00:42:35,219 --> 00:42:37,619
They wish us to leave.

392
00:42:37,688 --> 00:42:40,020
That cannot be.

393
00:42:40,091 --> 00:42:42,889
One saw us.

394
00:42:42,960 --> 00:42:45,155
lt ran off into the darkness.

395
00:42:45,229 --> 00:42:47,697
You are certain?

396
00:42:55,206 --> 00:42:57,367
Can you boys stay close to lvy here?

397
00:42:57,441 --> 00:43:01,070
She'll tell you some funny stories
and have you laughing soon.

398
00:43:09,320 --> 00:43:11,811
We will go together.

399
00:43:16,727 --> 00:43:18,718
<i>(children whimpering)</i>

400
00:44:08,579 --> 00:44:11,639
<i>(Alice) Livestock has been taken</i>
<i>and skinned.</i>

401
00:44:12,617 --> 00:44:15,085
The hides and feathers are missing.

402
00:44:15,152 --> 00:44:20,215
There are marks on the door
where it was opened.

403
00:44:23,094 --> 00:44:26,154
The marks are high.

404
00:44:26,230 --> 00:44:29,757
Coyotes cannot reach that height.

405
00:45:07,805 --> 00:45:09,636
<i>(gasps)</i>

406
00:45:32,196 --> 00:45:35,757
<i>(Alice)</i> The elders are going to have
an inquiry tomorrow.

407
00:45:35,833 --> 00:45:40,497
Each member of the village is to be
questioned in the meeting hall.

408
00:45:40,571 --> 00:45:42,937
<i>(Lucius)</i> To see how
the border was breached?

409
00:45:43,007 --> 00:45:44,998
<i>(Alice)</i> Yes.

410
00:45:49,847 --> 00:45:51,974
lt is cold outside.

411
00:45:52,049 --> 00:45:54,347
You ought to go in.

412
00:45:57,054 --> 00:46:00,683
Why are you on this porch?

413
00:46:00,758 --> 00:46:02,851
lt is not safe.

414
00:46:02,927 --> 00:46:05,191
There are other porches.

415
00:46:08,699 --> 00:46:11,463
Do you find me too much of a tomboy?

416
00:46:12,837 --> 00:46:15,533
l do long to do boy things...

417
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:19,676
...like that game
the boys play at the stump.

418
00:46:19,744 --> 00:46:22,542
They put their backs to the woods,

419
00:46:22,613 --> 00:46:26,481
and see how long they can wait
before getting scared.

420
00:46:28,452 --> 00:46:31,421
That's so exciting.

421
00:46:32,857 --> 00:46:35,291
l understand you hold the record.

422
00:46:36,494 --> 00:46:40,590
lt will never be broken, they say.

423
00:46:40,664 --> 00:46:44,191
lt's just children's games.

424
00:46:44,268 --> 00:46:48,500
How is it you are brave when all
the rest of us shake in our boots?

425
00:46:50,875 --> 00:46:56,541
l do not worry about what will happen,
only what needs to be done.

426
00:46:59,817 --> 00:47:01,808
How did you know l was here?

427
00:47:01,886 --> 00:47:04,218
l saw you out the window.

428
00:47:06,190 --> 00:47:08,090
No...

429
00:47:08,159 --> 00:47:11,094
...l won't tell you your color.

430
00:47:11,162 --> 00:47:13,756
Stop asking.

431
00:47:17,902 --> 00:47:22,066
When we are married,
will you dance with me?

432
00:47:22,139 --> 00:47:25,597
l find dancing very agreeable.

433
00:47:30,247 --> 00:47:33,307
Why can you not say what is in your head?

434
00:47:36,620 --> 00:47:39,680
Why can you not stop saying
what is in yours?

435
00:47:42,092 --> 00:47:46,290
Why must you lead, when l want to lead?

436
00:47:46,363 --> 00:47:50,026
lf l want to dance, l will ask you to dance.

437
00:47:50,100 --> 00:47:54,560
lf l want to speak,
l will open my mouth and speak.

438
00:47:55,773 --> 00:47:58,970
Everyone is forever
plaguing me to speak further.

439
00:48:00,544 --> 00:48:02,808
Why? What good is it to tell you

440
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:05,747
you are in my every thought
from the time l wake?

441
00:48:05,816 --> 00:48:09,377
What good can come from my saying
l-l sometimes cannot think clearly,

442
00:48:09,453 --> 00:48:12,354
or do my work properly?

443
00:48:12,423 --> 00:48:17,793
What gain can rise from my telling you
the only time l feel fear as others do...

444
00:48:19,597 --> 00:48:22,157
...is when l think of you in harm?

445
00:48:24,568 --> 00:48:27,696
That is why l am on this porch, lvy Walker.

446
00:48:29,974 --> 00:48:33,068
l fear for your safety before all others.

447
00:48:37,615 --> 00:48:39,606
And, yes...

448
00:48:41,285 --> 00:48:44,413
...l will dance with you
on our wedding night.

449
00:49:03,307 --> 00:49:05,901
<i>(woman) I had been to the storage shed</i>
<i>twice to fetch food</i>

450
00:49:05,976 --> 00:49:08,103
<i>prior to the wedding ceremony.</i>

451
00:49:08,178 --> 00:49:11,409
<i>(Alice) And the livestock</i>
<i>was untouched at that time?</i>

452
00:49:11,482 --> 00:49:14,883
<i>(woman) Yes, Mrs. Hunt.</i>
<i>All was as it should be.</i>

453
00:49:15,786 --> 00:49:18,186
Thank you, Beatrice.

454
00:49:25,062 --> 00:49:28,554
l beg your pardon.

455
00:49:28,632 --> 00:49:32,625
ls it true... about Lucius and lvy?

456
00:49:34,004 --> 00:49:36,837
There are whispers all over the village.

457
00:49:40,110 --> 00:49:44,945
We were informed early this morning
of their intentions.

458
00:49:45,015 --> 00:49:49,850
lt is amazing to witness
which two people love chooses to unite.

459
00:49:49,920 --> 00:49:52,480
lt follows no rules.

460
00:49:53,223 --> 00:49:55,054
Kitty...

461
00:49:55,125 --> 00:49:58,458
l wanted to speak with you first.

462
00:49:58,529 --> 00:50:03,592
l would not want you to feel pain,
in any fashion.

463
00:50:03,667 --> 00:50:06,795
You are my cherished one.

464
00:50:06,870 --> 00:50:11,204
lf you were to feel badly
about Lucius, l would not have it.

465
00:50:11,275 --> 00:50:15,473
One love to sacrifice
another love is not right.

466
00:50:20,417 --> 00:50:24,979
There is nothing you could do
that would sacrifice my love for you.

467
00:50:26,523 --> 00:50:29,583
You are my cherished one as well.

468
00:50:38,369 --> 00:50:41,236
God bless you and your life together.

469
00:50:50,314 --> 00:50:52,305
<i>(knock on door)</i>

470
00:51:01,558 --> 00:51:03,549
What's happened?

471
00:51:12,069 --> 00:51:14,970
ls this about lvy and myself?

472
00:51:26,316 --> 00:51:29,547
l know you are very fond of her.

473
00:51:29,620 --> 00:51:32,111
And l know she is fond of you.

474
00:51:38,262 --> 00:51:41,095
There are different types of love.

475
00:52:03,587 --> 00:52:05,487
Oh.

476
00:52:11,528 --> 00:52:13,689
Oh, God.

477
00:52:18,435 --> 00:52:20,266
<i>(moaning)</i>

478
00:52:28,779 --> 00:52:30,770
Oh, lvy...

479
00:52:34,985 --> 00:52:36,976
<i>(groans)</i>

480
00:52:54,037 --> 00:52:56,198
- <i>(knocking)</i>
- Noah?

481
00:52:57,307 --> 00:53:03,678
You'll be late for the meeting hall. Would
you like your father to walk you there?

482
00:53:03,747 --> 00:53:05,578
<i>(creaking)</i>

483
00:53:06,450 --> 00:53:08,281
Noah?

484
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:32,633
Oh...

485
00:53:32,709 --> 00:53:35,610
The bad... The bad color.

486
00:53:38,148 --> 00:53:39,979
Oh...

487
00:53:42,719 --> 00:53:46,416
The bad color, the bad color...

488
00:53:50,294 --> 00:53:52,728
<i>(music plays and dialogue muted)</i>

489
00:53:55,532 --> 00:53:57,056
Mama!

490
00:53:57,134 --> 00:53:59,659
<i>(door opens)</i>

491
00:54:03,941 --> 00:54:06,034
- l beg your pardon.
- What is it?

492
00:54:06,109 --> 00:54:08,703
There's been an accident.

493
00:54:20,624 --> 00:54:26,221
Noah Percy was found with quarts
of blood upon his clothes and hands.

494
00:54:26,830 --> 00:54:29,958
The blood was not his own,
and he will not speak as to whose it is.

495
00:54:30,033 --> 00:54:33,161
God in heaven.

496
00:54:33,237 --> 00:54:34,329
lvy!

497
00:54:35,372 --> 00:54:38,808
<i>(man)</i> ls there anyone injured in here?

498
00:54:38,876 --> 00:54:41,538
<i>(Alice)</i> Has anyone
been hurt in this home?

499
00:54:42,746 --> 00:54:44,771
ls anyone in here?

500
00:54:44,848 --> 00:54:47,783
<i>(Walker)</i> ls anyone hurt in this house?

501
00:54:54,324 --> 00:54:56,155
<i>(muttering)</i>

502
00:54:57,127 --> 00:55:00,585
22, 23, 24...

503
00:55:10,908 --> 00:55:14,105
31 , 32, 33...

504
00:55:33,597 --> 00:55:35,428
Lucius?

505
00:55:37,834 --> 00:55:39,825
Lucius Hunt!

506
00:55:40,737 --> 00:55:44,400
You answer me right this moment!

507
00:56:00,390 --> 00:56:02,381
<i>(distant voices)</i>

508
00:56:08,498 --> 00:56:11,160
<i>(Walker)</i> ls anyone hurt in this house?

509
00:56:13,170 --> 00:56:15,570
They're fine.

510
00:56:15,639 --> 00:56:17,630
Mr. Walker!

511
00:56:21,278 --> 00:56:23,269
<i>(Walker)</i> Joseph!

512
00:56:27,317 --> 00:56:32,619
Papa... l cannot see his color.

513
00:56:37,761 --> 00:56:39,388
lvy.

514
00:56:39,463 --> 00:56:41,454
- Come away. Come away.
- <i>(screams)</i>

515
00:56:41,531 --> 00:56:44,022
Come away. Here, take her.

516
00:56:44,101 --> 00:56:46,399
Take her.

517
00:56:46,470 --> 00:56:49,405
<i>(screams)</i> No!

518
00:56:52,876 --> 00:56:55,504
<i>(Mrs. Clack) He has suffered a great deal.</i>

519
00:56:57,614 --> 00:57:00,139
He may pass at any time.

520
00:57:04,588 --> 00:57:08,354
Please give him all your prayers
and good thoughts.

521
00:57:08,425 --> 00:57:10,655
He will hear them.

522
00:57:35,952 --> 00:57:38,318
<i>(door unlocking)</i>

523
00:57:56,907 --> 00:57:59,000
<i>(whimpering)</i>

524
00:58:01,078 --> 00:58:03,069
<i>(man)</i> Turn!

525
00:58:07,150 --> 00:58:08,981
<i>(groans)</i>

526
00:58:10,754 --> 00:58:12,585
<i>(crying)</i>

527
00:58:16,326 --> 00:58:18,658
<i>(yelling and banging)</i>

528
00:58:27,304 --> 00:58:29,898
<i>(Ivy) I am in love.</i>

529
00:58:30,574 --> 00:58:32,565
<i>(Walker)</i> l know.

530
00:58:33,510 --> 00:58:36,206
He is in love with me.

531
00:58:37,714 --> 00:58:39,705
l know.

532
00:58:40,884 --> 00:58:42,875
lf he dies...

533
00:58:44,955 --> 00:58:47,788
...all that is life to me will die with him.

534
00:58:51,194 --> 00:58:53,924
l ask permission...

535
00:58:55,532 --> 00:58:58,467
...to travel through Covington Woods...

536
00:59:01,671 --> 00:59:04,663
...and go to the towns...

537
00:59:06,109 --> 00:59:09,078
...to retrieve medicines...

538
00:59:11,615 --> 00:59:14,140
...that may save...

539
00:59:16,186 --> 00:59:18,177
...Lucius Hunt.

540
00:59:28,965 --> 00:59:31,934
You are my father.

541
00:59:32,002 --> 00:59:34,368
l will listen to you in all things.

542
00:59:37,107 --> 00:59:39,769
l will trust your decision.

543
00:59:45,182 --> 00:59:50,677
<i>(man) I</i>'<i>ve done what I can to close</i>
<i>the wounds. There</i>'<i>s an infection.</i>

544
00:59:50,754 --> 00:59:53,416
What can be done to mend him?

545
00:59:55,125 --> 00:59:57,389
We can only pray.

546
00:59:59,162 --> 01:00:02,495
lf there were no limitations,
what could be done?

547
01:00:04,668 --> 01:00:05,965
Hmm?

548
01:00:06,036 --> 01:00:08,368
What are you asking me?

549
01:00:12,475 --> 01:00:17,412
ls there anything at all
that can be done to mend the boy?

550
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:26,278
Please, Victor. Would you be so kind
as to answer my question?

551
01:00:34,798 --> 01:00:38,791
<i>(Victor) If the infection is contained,</i>
<i>he may still survive.</i>

552
01:00:41,705 --> 01:00:44,265
l must speak up.

553
01:00:45,875 --> 01:00:48,571
You have a restless spirit.

554
01:00:48,645 --> 01:00:51,170
l know the thing that is in your head.

555
01:00:53,416 --> 01:00:56,647
You're thinking of going to the towns.

556
01:00:57,621 --> 01:00:59,953
Tell me l'm wrong.

557
01:01:01,458 --> 01:01:07,419
You have made an oath, Edward,
as all have, never to go back.

558
01:01:07,497 --> 01:01:11,490
lt is a painful bargain,
but no good can come without sacrifice.

559
01:01:11,568 --> 01:01:14,935
These are your words l'm saying.
You cannot break the oath.

560
01:01:15,005 --> 01:01:17,496
- lt is sacred.
- lt is a crime,

561
01:01:17,574 --> 01:01:20,236
what has happened to Lucius.

562
01:01:21,978 --> 01:01:24,242
You have taken the oath.

563
01:01:24,314 --> 01:01:28,216
You and the rest of the elders...
Are you listening to me?

564
01:01:28,285 --> 01:01:30,276
You...

565
01:01:31,521 --> 01:01:34,285
...have taken the oath.

566
01:01:59,849 --> 01:02:05,185
The moment l heard my daughter's
vision had finally failed her,

567
01:02:05,255 --> 01:02:09,191
and that she would forever be blind,
l was sitting in that very chair.

568
01:02:12,028 --> 01:02:14,656
l was so ashamed.

569
01:02:18,902 --> 01:02:22,269
What do you know about your grandfather?

570
01:02:24,474 --> 01:02:27,637
He was the wealthiest man in the towns?

571
01:02:27,711 --> 01:02:30,874
That he was. He had a gift for that.

572
01:02:30,947 --> 01:02:36,943
lf he was given one dollar, in less than a
fortnight, he would have turned it into five.

573
01:02:37,854 --> 01:02:41,153
You do not know of money.
lt is not part of our life here.

574
01:02:41,224 --> 01:02:43,954
Money can be a wicked thing.

575
01:02:44,027 --> 01:02:48,157
lt can turn men's hearts black -
good men's hearts.

576
01:02:48,231 --> 01:02:51,997
My father could not see this.
For all his gifts,

577
01:02:52,068 --> 01:02:57,563
he was a poor judge of a man's character.
Your grandfather was a good man, lvy.

578
01:02:57,640 --> 01:03:00,131
He had a laugh that could
be heard three houses away.

579
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:03,270
He used to hold my hand as l hold yours.

580
01:03:03,346 --> 01:03:06,372
He taught me strength
and showed me love,

581
01:03:06,449 --> 01:03:12,513
and told me to lead
when others would only follow.

582
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:20,088
Your grandfather, James Walker,
died in his sleep.

583
01:03:20,163 --> 01:03:23,894
A man put a gun to his head
and shot him while he dreamed.

584
01:03:23,967 --> 01:03:30,031
l tell you this so you will understand
some of the reasons for my actions,

585
01:03:30,106 --> 01:03:31,835
and...

586
01:03:33,843 --> 01:03:36,175
...and the actions of others.

587
01:03:39,115 --> 01:03:43,518
You are a strong one, lvy.
You lead when others would follow.

588
01:03:43,586 --> 01:03:47,545
You see light
when there is only darkness.

589
01:03:52,295 --> 01:03:54,627
l trust you.

590
01:03:56,499 --> 01:04:00,367
l trust you among all others.

591
01:04:03,773 --> 01:04:06,298
Thank you, Father.

592
01:04:06,376 --> 01:04:09,004
lvy, do you know where you are?

593
01:04:10,547 --> 01:04:13,209
At the old shed that is not to be used.

594
01:04:15,885 --> 01:04:17,876
Yeah.

595
01:04:20,857 --> 01:04:23,223
- lvy.
- Yes, Father?

596
01:04:24,527 --> 01:04:27,018
Do your very best not to scream.

597
01:04:30,066 --> 01:04:32,227
<i>(door unlocking)</i>

598
01:04:32,302 --> 01:04:34,293
<i>(door opening)</i>

599
01:04:34,370 --> 01:04:36,804
What?

600
01:05:08,204 --> 01:05:12,971
l am leaving to fetch you medicines.

601
01:05:14,677 --> 01:05:17,475
l had a difficult time getting away.

602
01:05:17,547 --> 01:05:19,538
What is it?

603
01:05:22,485 --> 01:05:24,578
<i>(sighs)</i>

604
01:05:27,824 --> 01:05:30,315
lvy...

605
01:05:30,393 --> 01:05:32,384
...has asked...

606
01:05:33,530 --> 01:05:36,397
...to go to the towns...

607
01:05:36,466 --> 01:05:39,401
...for medicines.

608
01:05:42,238 --> 01:05:44,365
<i>(sniffing)</i>

609
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:50,111
<i>(footsteps approaching)</i>

610
01:07:19,302 --> 01:07:21,361
Christop.

611
01:07:26,142 --> 01:07:27,803
Christop...

612
01:07:27,877 --> 01:07:30,277
you needn't be scared.

613
01:07:31,381 --> 01:07:33,440
We have the magic rocks.

614
01:07:33,516 --> 01:07:35,541
They will keep us safe.

615
01:07:36,953 --> 01:07:40,719
Why have we not heard
of these rocks before?

616
01:07:41,290 --> 01:07:44,953
Christop, please.
Do not leave us.

617
01:07:45,028 --> 01:07:47,189
There is nothing to fear.

618
01:07:49,165 --> 01:07:52,066
Then why do you wear the cloak
of the safe color?

619
01:07:52,135 --> 01:07:54,899
We will light torches.

620
01:07:54,971 --> 01:07:57,769
lt will be safe.

621
01:07:57,840 --> 01:07:59,831
lt is forbidden.

622
01:08:01,444 --> 01:08:03,435
<i>(Finton)</i> Christop.

623
01:08:50,993 --> 01:08:52,927
lvy...

624
01:08:52,995 --> 01:08:55,759
there's something in these woods.

625
01:08:57,133 --> 01:08:59,567
lt turns my stomach to rot.

626
01:09:07,243 --> 01:09:12,510
You will be safe. They will not harm you,
because you cannot see.

627
01:09:12,582 --> 01:09:15,574
They will take pity on you,
the way they took pity on Noah

628
01:09:15,651 --> 01:09:18,313
when... when he ventured in the woods.

629
01:09:21,157 --> 01:09:24,092
They will kill me, lvy.

630
01:09:24,927 --> 01:09:27,122
l cannot stay.

631
01:09:33,136 --> 01:09:37,334
You're better in these woods
than most boys. Anyone would say so.

632
01:09:37,406 --> 01:09:40,239
lt is my burden, Finton.

633
01:09:42,178 --> 01:09:44,703
- You may go.
- Come with me.

634
01:10:12,675 --> 01:10:15,109
<i>(Walker) Do your very best not to scream.</i>

635
01:10:15,745 --> 01:10:17,736
<i>(door opens)</i>

636
01:10:29,759 --> 01:10:32,250
<i>(Ivy)</i> There's an odd smell.

637
01:10:36,999 --> 01:10:39,490
<i>(Walker)</i> lt is ahead of you.

638
01:10:41,170 --> 01:10:43,764
<i>(Ivy)</i> What is it?

639
01:10:43,840 --> 01:10:46,400
<i>(Walker)</i> l cannot explain in words.

640
01:10:47,944 --> 01:10:50,504
lt is just a few steps.

641
01:11:00,857 --> 01:11:02,188
<i>(screams)</i>

642
01:11:02,258 --> 01:11:07,457
- Those We Don't Speak Of!
- Do not be frightened.

643
01:11:08,264 --> 01:11:11,427
lt is only farce.

644
01:11:12,835 --> 01:11:17,602
Do not be frightened.

645
01:11:28,084 --> 01:11:33,886
There did exist rumors
of creatures in these woods.

646
01:11:33,956 --> 01:11:37,949
lt is in one of the history books
l used to teach in the towns.

647
01:11:38,828 --> 01:11:42,161
The screams from the woods?

648
01:11:44,000 --> 01:11:47,163
We created those sounds.

649
01:11:47,236 --> 01:11:49,761
The Ceremony of Meat?

650
01:11:49,839 --> 01:11:54,276
We remove it ourselves.
An elder is always assigned.

651
01:11:54,343 --> 01:11:57,676
The drills -
they are farce, too?

652
01:11:57,747 --> 01:12:01,080
We did not want anyone
to go to the towns, lvy.

653
01:12:03,819 --> 01:12:08,153
What about the animals -
the skinned ones?

654
01:12:08,224 --> 01:12:13,355
- Are the elders responsible for that, too?
- l believe one of the elders is responsible.

655
01:12:13,429 --> 01:12:15,693
lt will not happen again.

656
01:12:15,765 --> 01:12:19,667
There is no one in this village
who has not lost someone irreplaceable,

657
01:12:19,735 --> 01:12:26,402
who has not felt loss so deeply that they
questioned the very merit of living at all.

658
01:12:26,475 --> 01:12:28,966
lt is a darkness l wished...

659
01:12:29,979 --> 01:12:32,311
...you would never know.

660
01:12:34,617 --> 01:12:39,953
Forgive us our silly lies, lvy.
They were not meant to harm.

661
01:12:47,997 --> 01:12:53,128
l am... sad for you, Papa.

662
01:12:55,237 --> 01:12:58,070
For all the elders.

663
01:13:07,416 --> 01:13:12,251
On this paper has been written
a tool of medicine.

664
01:13:12,321 --> 01:13:14,346
lt is common in the towns.

665
01:13:14,423 --> 01:13:18,052
You will go... with two escorts.

666
01:13:18,728 --> 01:13:21,253
Follow the sounds of the stream.

667
01:13:21,330 --> 01:13:24,697
A half day's journey
will bring you to a hidden road.

668
01:13:24,767 --> 01:13:28,965
At this hidden road, the two escorts
will wait as you continue.

669
01:13:29,038 --> 01:13:33,202
You alone will follow the road...

670
01:13:34,744 --> 01:13:38,009
...and leave Covington Woods.

671
01:13:38,080 --> 01:13:42,949
You are to tell no one
in the towns where we are...

672
01:13:43,019 --> 01:13:45,419
...and return with haste.

673
01:13:48,124 --> 01:13:50,490
l cannot come with you.

674
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:58,024
You gave your heart to this boy.

675
01:13:59,935 --> 01:14:02,199
He is in need.

676
01:14:03,639 --> 01:14:07,234
Are you ready to take this burden,

677
01:14:07,309 --> 01:14:12,303
which, by right,
is yours and yours alone?

678
01:14:20,322 --> 01:14:25,021
l am making fresh cloths for Lucius.
He needs them.

679
01:14:25,094 --> 01:14:27,358
Alice, l've sent for help.

680
01:14:32,735 --> 01:14:34,726
l've sent lvy to the towns.

681
01:14:37,406 --> 01:14:39,397
You cannot.

682
01:14:41,710 --> 01:14:44,201
lt is all that l can give you.

683
01:14:52,321 --> 01:14:54,812
lt is all that l can give you.

684
01:14:59,161 --> 01:15:01,152
l accept.

685
01:15:21,417 --> 01:15:27,049
- What have you done?
- He is the victim of a crime.

686
01:15:27,123 --> 01:15:30,786
We have agreed never to go back. Never.

687
01:15:30,860 --> 01:15:33,351
What was the purpose of our leaving?

688
01:15:33,429 --> 01:15:38,560
Let us not forget it was out of hope
of something good and right.

689
01:15:38,634 --> 01:15:40,864
You should not have made
decisions without us.

690
01:15:40,936 --> 01:15:43,962
- You have gone too far.
- l'm guilty, Robert!

691
01:15:45,574 --> 01:15:49,704
l made a decision of the heart.
l cannot look into another's eyes

692
01:15:49,778 --> 01:15:55,182
and see the same look
l see in August's without justification!

693
01:15:55,251 --> 01:15:58,379
lt is too painful. l cannot bear it!

694
01:15:58,454 --> 01:16:01,548
You have jeopardized
everything we've made.

695
01:16:05,427 --> 01:16:09,090
Who do you think
will continue this place, this life?

696
01:16:11,634 --> 01:16:14,125
Do you plan to live forever?

697
01:16:15,804 --> 01:16:18,102
lt is in them that our future lies.

698
01:16:18,174 --> 01:16:22,873
lt is in lvy and Lucius that
this... this way of life will continue.

699
01:16:23,812 --> 01:16:26,940
Yes, l have risked! l hope l am always able

700
01:16:27,016 --> 01:16:30,713
to risk everything
for the just and right cause.

701
01:16:34,256 --> 01:16:39,023
lf we did not make this decision, we could
never again call ourselves innocent.

702
01:16:39,094 --> 01:16:44,430
And that, in the end, is what we
have protected here - innocence!

703
01:16:45,601 --> 01:16:48,263
That, l'm not ready to give up.

704
01:16:54,944 --> 01:16:57,003
Let her go.

705
01:16:59,481 --> 01:17:01,813
lf it ends, it ends.

706
01:17:05,588 --> 01:17:09,922
We can move towards hope.
lt's what's beautiful about this place.

707
01:17:10,993 --> 01:17:13,928
We must not run from heartache.

708
01:17:14,930 --> 01:17:16,955
You know, my brother
was slain in the towns.

709
01:17:17,032 --> 01:17:19,023
The rest of my family died here.

710
01:17:19,101 --> 01:17:22,593
Heartache is a part of life.
We know that now.

711
01:17:22,671 --> 01:17:25,538
lvy's running toward hope.
Let her run.

712
01:17:26,775 --> 01:17:30,734
lf this place is worthy,
she'll be successful in her quest.

713
01:17:33,649 --> 01:17:36,117
How could you have sent <i>her?</i>

714
01:17:36,185 --> 01:17:38,346
She's blind.

715
01:17:39,455 --> 01:17:43,255
She's more capable
than most in this village...

716
01:17:44,293 --> 01:17:48,059
...and she is led by love.

717
01:17:48,130 --> 01:17:51,588
The world moves for love.

718
01:17:53,836 --> 01:17:56,600
lt kneels before it in awe.

719
01:18:08,350 --> 01:18:12,184
? All the world to see

720
01:18:12,254 --> 01:18:16,452
? Time to look about and know

721
01:18:16,525 --> 01:18:20,655
? How the shadows come and go

722
01:18:20,729 --> 01:18:24,893
? How the breeze stirs the trees

723
01:18:24,967 --> 01:18:29,097
? How the blossoms grow

724
01:18:29,171 --> 01:18:33,232
? Sleep, baby, sleep

725
01:18:33,309 --> 01:18:37,143
? Sleep, gently sleep

726
01:19:05,341 --> 01:19:07,434
<i>(screams)</i>

727
01:19:24,993 --> 01:19:27,484
<i>(whimpering)</i>

728
01:19:51,954 --> 01:19:53,945
<i>(grunting)</i>

729
01:20:19,681 --> 01:20:21,672
<i>(gasping)</i>

730
01:20:25,754 --> 01:20:27,745
<i>(gasping)</i>

731
01:20:52,481 --> 01:20:57,145
<i>(Walker) There did exist rumors</i>
<i>of creatures in these woods.</i>

732
01:20:57,219 --> 01:20:59,744
<i>It is in one of the history books</i>
<i>I used to teach in the towns.</i>

733
01:20:59,822 --> 01:21:01,653
<i>(grunts)</i>

734
01:21:03,325 --> 01:21:05,156
<i>(crying)</i>

735
01:21:28,050 --> 01:21:29,881
<i>(gasps)</i>

736
01:21:33,322 --> 01:21:35,153
<i>(rustling)</i>

737
01:22:08,757 --> 01:22:10,588
<i>(rustling)</i>

738
01:22:24,806 --> 01:22:26,637
<i>(whimpering)</i>

739
01:22:30,412 --> 01:22:32,243
<i>(rustling)</i>

740
01:22:32,481 --> 01:22:34,312
<i>(crying)</i>

741
01:23:09,551 --> 01:23:11,382
<i>(growl)</i>

742
01:23:15,724 --> 01:23:17,555
<i>(growl)</i>

743
01:23:25,601 --> 01:23:28,001
lt is not real.

744
